# Product Development Workflow

- Do not silently reverse an explicit product decision. If a change conflicts
  with an established requirement, stop and ask before implementing it.
- Keep the runtime neural-only: no documents, retrieval, web search, citations,
  attachments, or knowledge packs unless the user explicitly changes scope.
- Use benchmark evidence before changing PAW graph composition or selecting a
  compiler/program.
- Keep Ask standalone by default, with context only through an explicit
  answer-anchored follow-up.
- Keep the primary UI limited to Ask and Prepare, without preset questions.
- After a requested product change: run relevant tests, build and install the
  latest macOS app, increment the version, commit all intended changes, push
  `main`, and publish the Apple Silicon DMG plus SHA-256 checksum as the latest
  GitHub release.
- Report factual limitations directly; do not describe compilation success as
  proof of factual accuracy.
